<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="259" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,582,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,654,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Description.</emphasis>
To 
<quantity box="[395,464,655,679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in height. Very thin shelled. Equivalve. Equilateral. Outline almost circular a little higher than long; anterior dorsal margin very short, horizontal; anterior curved, ventral slightly extended, posterior curved; posterior dorsal short sloping gently. Hinge plate smooth, edentulous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="259" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,582,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,762,787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Remarks.</emphasis>
In every respect these shells are identical with 
<taxonomicName box="[844,1011,762,787]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Axinulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="croulinensis">
<emphasis box="[844,1011,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">A. croulinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Atlantic Ocean (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1372,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 4. A" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,373,1872]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. A, Axinulus aff. croulinensis, Oman margin; B, Axinulus croulinensis Jeffreys, Loch Fyne, 40 m, Scotland, National Museum Wales; C, Axinulus undescribed, Gulf of Mexico, National Museum Wales; D, A. brevis Verrill &amp; Bush, Rockall Trough, 1595 m, National Museum Wales; E – F, Mendicula aff. ferruginosa, Oman margin; G – H, Mendicula ferruginosa Forbes, Rockall Trough, 1595 m, National Museum Wales; I, Leptaxinus indusarium Oliver &amp; Levin, holotype, National Museum Wales, NMWZ. 2005.34.1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236861/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">
Fig. 
<number box="[1356,1372,763,787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B). In the Atlantic 
<taxonomicName box="[294,463,798,823]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Axinulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="croulinensis">
<emphasis box="[294,463,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">A. croulinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded throughout and from depths a little as 
<quantity box="[1131,1191,799,823]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" unit="m" value="40.0">40 m</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[1231,1318,798,823]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8609999999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" unit="m" value="3861.0">3861 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Payne" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London Series B, 334, 481 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">
Payne &amp; Allen 
<number box="[222,282,835,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Zelaya" box="[303,462,834,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Zelaya, D. G. (2010) New species of Thyasira, Mendicula, and Axinulus (Bivalvia, Thyasiroidea) from Sub-Antarctic and Antarctic waters. Polar Biology, 33, 607 - 616." type="journal article" year="2010">
Zelaya (
<number box="[395,454,835,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
separated off the 
<collectingCountry box="[669,773,834,859]" name="Antarctica" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Antarctic</collectingCountry>
populations as 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelaya, 2010" authorityName="Zelaya" authorityYear="2010" box="[953,1267,834,859]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Axinulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="antarcticus">
<emphasis box="[953,1111,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">A. antarcticus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zelaya" box="[1119,1267,834,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Zelaya, D. G. (2010) New species of Thyasira, Mendicula, and Axinulus (Bivalvia, Thyasiroidea) from Sub-Antarctic and Antarctic waters. Polar Biology, 33, 607 - 616." type="journal article" year="2010">
Zelaya, 
<number box="[1211,1267,835,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but from shell characters there is little difference. The Atlantic abyssal 
<taxonomicName authority="Conrad, 1837" authorityName="Conrad" authorityYear="1837" box="[786,885,870,895]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mactridae" genus="Cryptodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Venerida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[786,885,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">A. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[901,968,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE 4. A" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,373,1872]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. A, Axinulus aff. croulinensis, Oman margin; B, Axinulus croulinensis Jeffreys, Loch Fyne, 40 m, Scotland, National Museum Wales; C, Axinulus undescribed, Gulf of Mexico, National Museum Wales; D, A. brevis Verrill &amp; Bush, Rockall Trough, 1595 m, National Museum Wales; E – F, Mendicula aff. ferruginosa, Oman margin; G – H, Mendicula ferruginosa Forbes, Rockall Trough, 1595 m, National Museum Wales; I, Leptaxinus indusarium Oliver &amp; Levin, holotype, National Museum Wales, NMWZ. 2005.34.1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236861/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">
Fig. 
<number box="[954,968,871,895]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E) has a more tear-drop shaped shell with a distinct anterior slope while an undescribed species (
<figureCitation box="[757,824,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 4. A" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,373,1872]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. A, Axinulus aff. croulinensis, Oman margin; B, Axinulus croulinensis Jeffreys, Loch Fyne, 40 m, Scotland, National Museum Wales; C, Axinulus undescribed, Gulf of Mexico, National Museum Wales; D, A. brevis Verrill &amp; Bush, Rockall Trough, 1595 m, National Museum Wales; E – F, Mendicula aff. ferruginosa, Oman margin; G – H, Mendicula ferruginosa Forbes, Rockall Trough, 1595 m, National Museum Wales; I, Leptaxinus indusarium Oliver &amp; Levin, holotype, National Museum Wales, NMWZ. 2005.34.1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236861/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">
Fig. 
<number box="[809,824,907,931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C) from the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1047,1132,906,931]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Mexico</collectingCountry>
is distinctly oblique. Other species cited in WoRMS under 
<taxonomicName box="[516,614,942,967]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Axinulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[516,614,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Axinulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not conform and need reassignment or placed in as yet undescribed genera. The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[369,489,979,1002]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Genaxinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[369,489,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Genaxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct with the very characteristic elevated adductor scars with species known from the Atlantic and SE 
<collectingCountry box="[448,554,1014,1039]" name="Australia" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Australia</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="M. Sars, 1870" authorityName="M. Sars" authorityYear="1870" box="[568,983,1015,1039]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Genaxinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="eumyarius">
<emphasis box="[568,813,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Genaxinus eumyarius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sars" box="[822,983,1015,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Sars, M. (1870) Bidrag til Kundskab om Christiania-fjordens Fauna. Efter Forfatterens efterladte Manuskripter samlet og udgivet af hans Son. Johan Dahlk, Vol. II, 1 - 145." type="book chapter" year="1870">
M. Sars, 
<number box="[927,983,1015,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1870.0">1870</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hedley, 1907" authorityName="Hedley" authorityYear="1907" box="[1042,1432,1014,1039]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Genaxinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="albigena">
<emphasis box="[1042,1269,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Genaxinus albigena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hedley" box="[1278,1432,1014,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Hedley, C. (1907) The results of the deep sea investigations in the Tasman Sea II. The expedition of the '' Woy Woy' '. Records of the Australian Museum, 6, 356 - 364. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.6.1907.1020" type="journal article" year="1907">
Hedley, 
<number box="[1373,1432,1015,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1907.0">1907</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bernard, 1979" authorityName="Bernard" authorityYear="1979" box="[151,505,1050,1075]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Axinulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="careyi">
<emphasis box="[151,329,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Axinulus careyi</emphasis>
Bernard, 
<number box="[449,505,1051,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</taxonomicName>
has the appearance of a 
<taxonomicName box="[805,925,1050,1075]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Mendicula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[805,925,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Mendicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Okutani, Fujikura &amp; Kojima, 1999" authorityName="Okutani, Fujikura &amp; Kojima" authorityYear="1999" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Axinulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hadalis">
<emphasis box="[988,1180,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Axinulus hadalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Okutani" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Okutani, O., Fujikura, K. &amp; Kojima, S. (1999) Two new hadal bivalves of the Family Thyasiridae from the convergent area of the Japan Trench. Venus, 58 (2), 49 - 59." type="journal article" year="1999">
Okutani, Fujikura &amp; Kojima, 
<number box="[248,305,1087,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Valentich-Scott &amp; Coan, 2012" authorityName="Valentich-Scott &amp; Coan" authorityYear="2012" box="[368,978,1086,1111]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Axinulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="thackergeigeri">
<emphasis box="[368,635,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Axinulus thackergeigeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Valentich-Scott" box="[642,978,1086,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Coan, E. V. &amp; Valentich-Scott, P. (2012) Bivalve Seashells of Tropical West America. Marine Bivalve Mollusks from Baja California to Northern Peru. Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History Monographs Number 6, Part 1, pp. 1 - 596." type="book chapter" year="2012">
Valentich-Scott &amp; Coan, 
<quantity box="[922,978,1087,1111]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11048" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" unit="in" value="2012.0">2012</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Coan" box="[1014,1350,1086,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Coan, E. V. &amp; Valentich-Scott, P. (2012) Bivalve Seashells of Tropical West America. Marine Bivalve Mollusks from Baja California to Northern Peru. Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History Monographs Number 6, Part 1, pp. 1 - 596." type="book chapter" year="2012">
Coan &amp; Valentich-Scott, 
<number box="[1294,1350,1087,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
require novel placement.
</paragraph>
